menu "HTTP Fetch"

    config HTTP_FETCH_MAX_CONCURRENT_TLS
        int "Max concurrent TLS sessions through http_fetch"
        range 1 8
        default 2
        help
            Upper bound on how many HTTP(S) transfers issued through the shared
            http_fetch helper may hold a live TLS session at the same time. A
            counting semaphore in do_fetch() blocks the (N+1)-th concurrent fetch
            until an in-flight one releases its slot.

            This caps the concurrent-TLS contention on the single Wi-Fi link that
            starves large downloads: a socket read stalls past its timeout, lwIP
            returns EAGAIN (logged as "esp_tls_conn_read error, errno=No more
            processes"), esp_http_client reports it as end-of-stream, and the
            transfer is retried as a truncated read. Big GIFs could lose every
            retry. See docs/concurrent-tls-eagain-tabled.md (Option 4).

            2 preserves the Giphy API-page-fetch + binary-download overlap that
            cold-start latency depends on, while blocking a third session from
            piling on during a refresh burst. Set to 1 to fully serialize all
            http_fetch transfers if 2 still shows contention.

            Note: this gates only transfers that go through http_fetch. The
            persistent Makapix MQTT-over-TLS link runs on a separate stack and is
            not gated (it benefits indirectly from the reduced HTTP contention).

endmenu
